    {%- comment -%}
      Drawer-toggle click intercept (added 2026-04-28; rewritten 2026-04-28
      after a Cloudflare-bot-challenge regression).

      Background: header cart icon and other [data-drawer-toggle] buttons
      have BOTH href={routes.cart_url} (link fallback) AND a click handler
      bound by deferred theme.js that does preventDefault and opens the
      drawer. On fast pages — or when theme.js fails to fully load (e.g.,
      after a Cloudflare bot-detection challenge throttles the user's IP) —
      the click falls through to link navigation and the user lands on the
      standalone /cart page instead of seeing the drawer.

      First version (queue + replay on DOMContentLoaded) caused a worse
      regression: the synthetic queued.click() replay needed theme.js's
      button-level handler to be bound by replay-time. If theme.js had
      not bound (Cloudflare-induced loading delay/failure), the replayed
      click bubbled to the link href and navigated.

      This version is self-contained: capture-phase listener at document
      level intercepts every [data-drawer-toggle] click, preventDefault +
      stopImmediatePropagation (suppresses theme.js's redundant button-
      level handler), and dispatches theme:drawer:toggle DIRECTLY on the
      matched drawer element. The Drawer instance's listener (bound in
      theme.js's drawer constructor at section-load time) handles toggle.

      Works whether or not theme.js's connectToggle bound its own click
      handler — only depends on the Drawer instance existing in DOM and
      its toggle listener being attached. If theme.js fails entirely
      (no Drawer instance), click does nothing — better than wrong /cart
      navigation. ~450 bytes inline cost, runs before first paint.
    {%- endcomment -%}
    <script>
      (function () {
        document.addEventListener('click', function (e) {
          var btn = e.target.closest && e.target.closest('[data-drawer-toggle]');
          if (!btn) return;
          var key = btn.getAttribute('data-drawer-toggle');
          var drawer = document.querySelector('[data-drawer="' + key + '"]');
          if (!drawer) return; // no drawer in DOM, let link fallback navigate
          e.preventDefault();
          e.stopImmediatePropagation();
          drawer.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent('theme:drawer:toggle', { bubbles: false }));
        }, true);
      })();
    </script>
    {%- comment -%}
      Web Vitals RUM reporter — added 2026-04-28.

      Captures real-shopper CLS, LCP, INP, FCP via PerformanceObserver
      and pushes to window.dataLayer for GTM forwarding to GA4.
      Solves the "PSI is too noisy to trust as a perf metric" problem
      we hit today (single-run PSI swings 19↔37↔PAGE_HUNG within
      minutes — see beads e4a notes).

      Why inline in head: PerformanceObserver with buffered:true must
      be created before the events fire to capture them. Loading from
      an external file means missing the early entries.

      Cost: ~600 bytes minified inline. Zero network requests, zero
      user-facing change. Listeners only fire on page lifecycle events
      (pagehide for LCP/CLS finalization, every interaction for INP).

      Receives in GTM:
        event: web_vital
        web_vital_name: CLS | LCP | INP | FCP
        web_vital_value: number (ms for time metrics, score for CLS)
        web_vital_id: short attribution string (LCP element tag, INP
          interaction target, etc) — for slicing in GA4

      GTM tag setup is admin-side: see beads 7fz for the GA4
      attribution wiring; this commit ships the data emission. Without
      the GTM tag, dataLayer.push silently no-ops; no-op on browsers
      missing PerformanceObserver too.
    {%- endcomment -%}
    <script>
      (function () {
        if (!('PerformanceObserver' in window)) return;
        var dl = (window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || []);
        var send = function (name, value, id) {
          dl.push({
            event: 'web_vital',
            web_vital_name: name,
            web_vital_value: Math.round(value * 1000) / 1000,
            web_vital_id: id || ''
          });
        };
        // CLS — sum of all unexpected layout shifts
        var clsValue = 0;
        try {
          new PerformanceObserver(function (l) {
            l.getEntries().forEach(function (e) { if (!e.hadRecentInput) clsValue += e.value; });
          }).observe({ type: 'layout-shift', buffered: true });
        } catch (e) {}
        // LCP — largest contentful paint
        var lcpValue = 0, lcpId = '';
        try {
          new PerformanceObserver(function (l) {
            var entries = l.getEntries();
            var last = entries[entries.length - 1];
            if (last) {
              lcpValue = last.startTime;
              lcpId = (last.element && last.element.tagName) ? last.element.tagName.toLowerCase() : '';
              if (last.url) lcpId += '|' + last.url.split('/').pop().slice(0, 40);
            }
          }).observe({ type: 'largest-contentful-paint', buffered: true });
        } catch (e) {}
        // FCP — first contentful paint (one-shot)
        try {
          new PerformanceObserver(function (l) {
            var fcp = l.getEntries()[0];
            if (fcp) send('FCP', fcp.startTime);
          }).observe({ type: 'paint', buffered: true });
        } catch (e) {}
        // INP — worst Event Timing entry over the page lifetime
        var worstInp = 0, worstInpId = '';
        try {
          new PerformanceObserver(function (l) {
            l.getEntries().forEach(function (e) {
              if (e.duration > worstInp) {
                worstInp = e.duration;
                worstInpId = e.name + (e.target && e.target.tagName ? ':' + e.target.tagName.toLowerCase() : '');
              }
            });
          }).observe({ type: 'event', buffered: true, durationThreshold: 16 });
        } catch (e) {}
        // Send finalized metrics on page hide (bfcache-safe, no double-fire)
        addEventListener('pagehide', function () {
          if (lcpValue > 0) send('LCP', lcpValue, lcpId);
          send('CLS', clsValue);
          if (worstInp > 0) send('INP', worstInp, worstInpId);
        }, { once: true });
      })();
    </script>
