      wrapper that delayed the cart fetch until the main thread was idle.
      That delay was several hundred ms on a busy page (especially after
      today's perf-defer push pushed jquery + theme.js + storepickup.js +
      vendor.js into the deferred queue). Without the cart pre-fetched,
      opening the slide-out drawer triggered an on-demand /cart.js fetch
      and rendered the loading skeleton for several seconds. Eager dispatch
      starts the fetch the moment pageshow fires, so by user-click time
      this.cart is usually populated and CartItems.loadHTML() runs instantly.

      Kept the pageshow event (not a one-shot timer) so bfcache restores
      also re-fire the cart init — important for back-button navigation.

      Cost: a /cart.js fetch a few hundred ms earlier than before. /cart.js
      is async, never render-blocking, so this doesn't move LCP/FCP.
    {%- endcomment -%}
